---
/*
  /proof/pericyte-correction — the central worked example.

  The Borrowed Light essay's pericyte paragraph (Halliday → Nation →
  Montagne → Correction event → dependencies notified) made
  interactive. Four scroll stops. Each stop is a real primitive
  (Finding, EvidenceObject, Correction, ConfidenceUpdate) with a
  signature, a delta, and a small visual showing the dependency graph
  responding. The substrate seen working, end-to-end.

  This is the page that converts skeptics. It is not a doc; it is an
  illustration of one Correction event landing in a real frontier and
  changing what the next reader inherits.

  Names + papers are real (Halliday 2016, Nation 2019, Montagne 2020).
  vf_/vfr_/vrev_ ids are illustrative — they're shaped exactly like
  what the substrate generates, but seeded so the page reproduces
  byte-identically across reloads.
*/
import Reading from "../../layouts/Reading.astro";
import Imprint from "../../components/Imprint.astro";
---

<Reading
  title="A worked Correction · Vela"
  description="One Correction event, end-to-end: how a 2020 paper narrowed the scope of a 2016 finding and notified its dependents."
  active="docs"
>
  <header class="page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow">Proof · worked example</p>
    <h1 class="page-head__title">A worked Correction</h1>
    <p class="page-head__sub">One event, end-to-end. The substrate seen working.</p>
  </header>

  <article class="wc">
    <p class="wc__lede">
      Three real papers (Halliday 2016, Nation 2019, Montagne 2020). Four signed events.
      One Correction propagating through a dependency graph to three downstream objects.
      Reconstructed from the actual literature; the substrate-mediated propagation shows
      what would have happened if Vela had existed in 2020. Confidence numbers are
      illustrative; the event shapes and propagation paths are the load-bearing claim.
    </p>

    <!-- ── Stop 1 — the original finding ── -->
    <section class="wc__stop" id="stop-1" data-step="1">
      <div class="wc__stop-head">
        <span class="wc__date">2026-01-08</span>
        <span class="wc__sep">·</span>
        <span class="wc__primitive">Finding</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="wc__stop-title">The original finding lands.</h2>
      <p class="wc__line">
        Halliday and colleagues post-mortem work on hippocampal pericyte degeneration is
        compiled into a Vela finding by an agent and accepted by a reviewer.
      </p>

      <article class="wc__card">
        <header class="wc__card-head">
          <span class="wc__card-id">vf_4a91ce…</span>
          <span class="wc__sep">·</span>
          <span class="wc__card-state wc__card-state--ok">supported</span>
          <span class="wc__sep">·</span>
          <span class="wc__card-conf">conf <span class="wc__card-conf-num">0.62</span></span>
        </header>
        <p class="wc__assertion">
          Pericyte loss precedes cognitive decline in early Alzheimer's disease.
        </p>
        <dl class="wc__fields">
          <div class="wc__field"><dt>scope</dt><dd>human · sporadic AD · prodromal stage</dd></div>
          <div class="wc__field"><dt>evidence</dt><dd>1 EvidenceObject · postmortem hippocampal histology</dd></div>
          <div class="wc__field"><dt>cite</dt><dd><em>Halliday et al., J Cereb Blood Flow Metab 2016</em></dd></div>
          <div class="wc__field"><dt>signed by</dt><dd>reviewer:halliday-lab → vrev_71f2…</dd></div>
        </dl>
      </article>

      <p class="wc__caption">
        At this point the constellation has one node here. No dependents yet.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Stop 2 — new evidence raises confidence ── -->
    <section class="wc__stop" id="stop-2" data-step="2">
      <div class="wc__stop-head">
        <span class="wc__date">2026-04-14</span>
        <span class="wc__sep">·</span>
        <span class="wc__primitive">EvidenceObject</span>
        <span class="wc__sep">·</span>
        <span class="wc__primitive wc__primitive--soft">ConfidenceUpdate</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="wc__stop-title">New evidence attaches. Confidence rises.</h2>
      <p class="wc__line">
        Nation and colleagues' longitudinal MRI study showing blood-brain-barrier
        leakage as an early biomarker of cognitive dysfunction is added as a second
        EvidenceObject. The reviewer signs a ConfidenceUpdate; the same finding now
        carries 0.78.
      </p>

      <div class="wc__delta">
        <div class="wc__delta-row">
          <span class="wc__delta-side">before</span>
          <span class="wc__delta-bar"><span class="wc__delta-fill" style="width:62%;"></span></span>
          <span class="wc__delta-num">0.62</span>
        </div>
        <div class="wc__delta-row">
          <span class="wc__delta-side wc__delta-side--gold">after</span>
          <span class="wc__delta-bar"><span class="wc__delta-fill wc__delta-fill--gold" style="width:78%;"></span></span>
          <span class="wc__delta-num">0.78</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <article class="wc__event">
        <header class="wc__event-head">
          <span class="wc__event-tag">ConfidenceUpdate</span>
          <span class="wc__event-id">vrev_3c7e91…</span>
        </header>
        <dl class="wc__fields">
          <div class="wc__field"><dt>target</dt><dd>vf_4a91ce…</dd></div>
          <div class="wc__field"><dt>delta</dt><dd>+0.16 (0.62 → 0.78)</dd></div>
          <div class="wc__field"><dt>cite</dt><dd><em>Nation et al., Nature Medicine 2019</em></dd></div>
          <div class="wc__field"><dt>signed by</dt><dd>reviewer:nation-mri → Ed25519 over canonical preimage</dd></div>
          <div class="wc__field"><dt>signed at</dt><dd>2026-04-14T11:42:08Z</dd></div>
        </dl>
      </article>

      <p class="wc__caption">
        Same node, brighter. Two EvidenceObjects attached.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Stop 3 — the correction lands ── -->
    <section class="wc__stop" id="stop-3" data-step="3">
      <div class="wc__stop-head">
        <span class="wc__date">2026-06-02</span>
        <span class="wc__sep">·</span>
        <span class="wc__primitive wc__primitive--accent">Correction</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="wc__stop-title">A 2020 paper narrows the scope.</h2>
      <p class="wc__line">
        Montagne and colleagues' 2020 paper showing the BBB breakdown is concentrated in
        APOE4 carriers lands. A reviewer drafts a Correction event and signs it.
        The scope narrows from <em>sporadic AD</em> to <em>APOE4-positive sporadic AD</em>;
        confidence on the broader claim drops; a new child Finding spawns for the APOE4-positive subgroup.
      </p>

      <article class="wc__event wc__event--correction">
        <header class="wc__event-head">
          <span class="wc__event-tag wc__event-tag--accent">Correction</span>
          <span class="wc__event-id">vrev_b0144a…</span>
        </header>
        <dl class="wc__fields">
          <div class="wc__field"><dt>target</dt><dd>vf_4a91ce…</dd></div>
          <div class="wc__field"><dt>scope before</dt><dd>human · sporadic AD · prodromal stage</dd></div>
          <div class="wc__field"><dt>scope after</dt><dd>human · sporadic AD · prodromal stage · APOE4-positive</dd></div>
          <div class="wc__field"><dt>confidence on broader claim</dt><dd>0.78 → 0.41</dd></div>
          <div class="wc__field"><dt>spawns</dt><dd>vf_d92710… (APOE4-positive subgroup, conf 0.74)</dd></div>
          <div class="wc__field"><dt>cite</dt><dd><em>Montagne et al., Nature 2020</em></dd></div>
          <div class="wc__field"><dt>signed by</dt><dd>reviewer:nakamura-v10 → Ed25519</dd></div>
          <div class="wc__field"><dt>signed at</dt><dd>2026-06-02T16:19:33Z</dd></div>
        </dl>
      </article>

      <div class="wc__delta">
        <div class="wc__delta-row">
          <span class="wc__delta-side">broader</span>
          <span class="wc__delta-bar"><span class="wc__delta-fill wc__delta-fill--cinnabar" style="width:41%;"></span></span>
          <span class="wc__delta-num">0.41</span>
        </div>
        <div class="wc__delta-row">
          <span class="wc__delta-side wc__delta-side--gold">APOE4+</span>
          <span class="wc__delta-bar"><span class="wc__delta-fill wc__delta-fill--gold" style="width:74%;"></span></span>
          <span class="wc__delta-num">0.74</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="wc__caption">
        The constellation now has two nodes here, linked by a parent-of relationship.
        The original is dimmer; the child is brighter; the seam is visible.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Stop 4 — dependents notified ── -->
    <section class="wc__stop" id="stop-4" data-step="4">
      <div class="wc__stop-head">
        <span class="wc__date">2026-06-04 → 2026-07-11</span>
        <span class="wc__sep">·</span>
        <span class="wc__primitive">Dependency notification</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="wc__stop-title">Three downstream objects find out.</h2>
      <p class="wc__line">
        The dependency graph notifies three objects that previously rested on
        the broader claim. None of these teams talked. None of them needed to.
        The substrate carried the correction.
      </p>

      <ul class="wc__deps">
        <li class="wc__dep">
          <header class="wc__dep-head">
            <span class="wc__dep-when">+ 2 days</span>
            <span class="wc__sep">·</span>
            <span class="wc__dep-where">biotech · Cambridge MA</span>
          </header>
          <p class="wc__dep-body">
            A target hypothesis at one neurovascular biotech updates its priors:
            the program redirects from a sporadic-AD pan-cohort design to an
            APOE4-stratified Phase Ib. The portfolio review the next Friday
            takes thirty minutes instead of three weeks.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="wc__dep">
          <header class="wc__dep-head">
            <span class="wc__dep-when">+ 39 days</span>
            <span class="wc__sep">·</span>
            <span class="wc__dep-where">review article · Osaka</span>
          </header>
          <p class="wc__dep-body">
            A review article's headline claim picks up a margin gloss: the
            broader pericyte-loss-precedes claim is annotated with the APOE4
            stratification before the proof galley is signed. The reader sees
            both lines on first read.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="wc__dep">
          <header class="wc__dep-head">
            <span class="wc__dep-when">+ next protocol-amendment cycle</span>
            <span class="wc__sep">·</span>
            <span class="wc__dep-where">trial · Toronto</span>
          </header>
          <p class="wc__dep-body">
            A Phase II inclusion criterion that depended on the broader claim
            is flagged for review at the sponsor's next protocol-amendment
            window. The flag carries a back-link to <code>vrev_b0144a…</code> so
            the data-monitoring committee, the IRB, and any future auditor see
            the same reasoning when the amendment is drafted. Trials run on
            their own clocks; the substrate does not pretend otherwise.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p class="wc__caption">
        The biotech moves in days, the review article on the next galley cycle, the
        trial on its own protocol-amendment window. Each downstream object updates
        on the clock its institution actually runs on — but every one of them
        starts from the same signed Correction event instead of rumor or a chance
        encounter at a conference. In the world the essay describes, the same loop
        typically takes <span class="wc__num">five to twelve years</span>, when it
        closes at all.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Closing ── -->
    <section class="wc__closing">
      <p class="wc__close-line">
        <em>This is one Correction event. The substrate carries millions.</em>
      </p>
      <p class="wc__close-sub">
        Every Finding above is a content-addressed object. Every event is signed.
        Two implementations replay this same sequence and reduce to the same hash,
        or one of them is wrong. That is the only invariant the protocol promises;
        it is enough to make the field navigable.
      </p>
      <p class="wc__close-cta">
        <a class="wc__cta-link" href="/workbench">Open the workbench →</a>
        <span class="wc__sep">·</span>
        <a class="wc__cta-link" href="/spec">Read the spec →</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <Imprint returnHref="/spec" returnLabel="Back to the spec" />
  </article>

</Reading>

<style>
  .aside-link {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--size-imprint);
    letter-spacing: var(--track-imprint);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
    transition: color var(--dur-1) var(--ease), border-bottom-color var(--dur-1) var(--ease);
  }
  .aside-link:hover {
    color: var(--gold);
    border-bottom-color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 56%, transparent);
  }

  .wc {
    max-width: var(--measure-wide);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0;
  }

  /* ── Lede ── */
  .wc__lede {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    margin: 0 0 var(--rhythm-section);
    max-width: 70ch;
  }

  /* ── Each scroll stop ── */
  .wc__stop {
    margin: 0 0 clamp(3rem, 7vh, 4.5rem);
    padding-top: 1.2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 28%, transparent);
  }
  .wc__stop-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 6px 8px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--size-kicker);
    letter-spacing: var(--track-imprint);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 72%, var(--ink-2));
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
  }
  .wc__date {
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
  .wc__primitive { color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 80%, var(--ink-2)); font-weight: 500; }
  .wc__primitive--soft { color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 56%, var(--ink-3)); }
  .wc__primitive--accent { color: var(--cinnabar); }
  .wc__sep { color: var(--ink-4); }

  .wc__stop-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.1rem);
    line-height: 1.18;
    letter-spacing: var(--track-display);
    color: var(--ink-0);
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
    max-width: 32ch;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .wc__line {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    line-height: var(--leading-read);
    color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--ink-1) 88%, var(--ink-2));
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    max-width: 56ch;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .wc__line em { font-style: italic; color: var(--ink-1); }

  .wc__caption {
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--ink-3) 92%, transparent);
    max-width: 60ch;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .wc__num { color: var(--ink-1); font-weight: 500; }

  /* ── Finding card ── */
  .wc__card {
    background: var(--paper-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 1.2rem 1.4rem 1.3rem;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 38rem;
  }
  .wc__card-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 6px 8px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
  }
  .wc__card-id { color: var(--ink-2); letter-spacing: 0.02em; text-transform: none; font-size: 11px; }
  .wc__card-state {
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--moss) 38%, transparent);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    color: var(--moss);
  }
  .wc__card-state--ok { color: var(--moss); border-color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--moss) 38%, transparent); }
  .wc__card-conf { color: var(--ink-3); }
  .wc__card-conf-num { color: var(--ink-1); font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }

  .wc__assertion {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.32;
    letter-spacing: var(--track-display);
    color: var(--ink-0);
    margin: 0 0 0.95rem;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }

  .wc__fields {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .wc__field {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 160px 1fr;
    gap: 12px;
    padding: 8px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-1);
    align-items: baseline;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .wc__field:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  .wc__field dt {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--ink-3) 88%, transparent);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .wc__field dd {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    color: var(--ink-1);
  }
  .wc__field dd em { font-family: var(--font-body); font-style: italic; font-size: 13px; color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--ink-1) 88%, var(--ink-2)); }
  .wc__field dd code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.92em;
    color: var(--ink-1);
    background: var(--paper-1);
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xs);
  }

  /* ── Event card (ConfidenceUpdate, Correction) ── */
  .wc__event {
    margin: 1.4rem 0 0;
    padding: 1.05rem 1.35rem 1.2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 38%, transparent);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
    background: transparent;
    max-width: 42rem;
  }
  .wc__event--correction {
    border-top: 2px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--cinnabar) 56%, transparent);
  }
  .wc__event-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .wc__event-tag {
    color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 72%, var(--ink-2));
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .wc__event-tag--accent { color: var(--cinnabar); }
  .wc__event-id {
    color: var(--ink-3);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    text-transform: none;
    font-size: 11px;
  }

  /* ── Delta bars (before / after) ── */
  .wc__delta {
    margin: 1.2rem 0 0;
    max-width: 32rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
  }
  .wc__delta-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr 60px;
    gap: 12px;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .wc__delta-side {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .wc__delta-side--gold { color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 76%, var(--ink-2)); }
  .wc__delta-bar {
    display: block;
    height: 4px;
    background: var(--rule-1);
    position: relative;
    border-radius: 2px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .wc__delta-fill {
    display: block;
    height: 100%;
    background: var(--ink-3);
    transition: width 600ms var(--ease);
  }
  .wc__delta-fill--gold { background: var(--gold); }
  .wc__delta-fill--cinnabar { background: var(--cinnabar); opacity: 0.78; }
  .wc__delta-num {
    text-align: right;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--ink-1);
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  /* ── Dependents list ── */
  .wc__deps {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
  }
  .wc__dep {
    padding: 1.1rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-1);
  }
  .wc__dep:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  .wc__dep-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 0.55rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .wc__dep-when {
    color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 76%, var(--ink-2));
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .wc__dep-where {
    color: var(--ink-2);
    text-transform: none;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    font-size: 11px;
  }
  .wc__dep-body {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--ink-1) 90%, var(--ink-2));
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 60ch;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .wc__dep-body code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.86em;
    color: var(--ink-1);
    background: var(--paper-1);
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xs);
  }

  /* ── Closing ── */
  .wc__closing {
    margin: clamp(3rem, 8vh, 5rem) 0 0;
    padding-top: 1.6rem;
    border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 38%, transparent);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }
  .wc__close-line {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: clamp(1.45rem, 2.8vw, 1.95rem);
    line-height: 1.32;
    letter-spacing: var(--track-display);
    color: var(--ink-0);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    max-width: 38ch;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .wc__close-sub {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--ink-2) 92%, transparent);
    margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
    max-width: 60ch;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .wc__close-cta {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .wc__cta-link {
    color: var(--ink-1);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 56%, transparent);
